      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MRS. TIGGYWINKLE (8) has a strong record this journey with two wins and a minor from six starts. Comes off a (22.22) win last time, scoring by 1.5 lengths in a Rank Limit - Grade 7 over 390m at Ballarat. Looks suited here and rates on top. CHEER DOWN (1) goes very well at the course and distance with two wins and a placing from five starts. Placed last time (23.17) at this track in a T3 RSTW, finishing second and beaten 1.5 lengths. Can feature with the right run. CHORUS LINE (2) turned in a better run last time to find a minor placing (24.78) at Sale behind Dr. Tessa in a Bottom Up - Grade 6. Has the pace to be prominent. Remains without a win from the draw but has been in the placings four times from six attempts. Winning chance. HANDFUL OF CASH (4) cannot be overlooked following a recent narrow defeat.",
